# Gladdis Workshop Context

- Treat Gladdis as an Electron workshop, not a chatbot: React conversation UI on the left, native `WebContentsView` Chromium tabs plus CDP on the right, with local filesystem and shell access.
- Trust live code over stale overviews or confident docstrings. If docs disagree with implementation, verify behavior in `src/main/`, `src/renderer/`, and `shared/` before changing code.
- The live browser automation path is agent-in-the-loop: API providers use `models/agentLoopRunner.ts`, Codex uses dynamic `gladdis.*` tools, and Claude Code uses the local bridge. All routes ultimately drive `BrowserTools.run(...)`.
- Prefer `grep_page` and `read_a11y` for perception. Use `read_page` for orientation. Use screenshots only as a fallback for genuinely visual or unlabeled content.
- Use `grep_click` and `grep_type` when an action can be discovered and performed from grep or a `read_a11y` `@aN` ref (`click_xy` also accepts `ref`).
- The old deterministic `src/main/pipeline/` engine and its `browse_task` tool were retired; the agentic perceive/drive loop is now the only browser-automation path. The shared `LlmComplete` type lives in `src/main/models/llm.ts`.
- For IPC changes, keep the main process, preload bridge, renderer callers, and shared API/type contracts in sync.
- Local Cursor MCP config can contain bearer tokens. Do not expose or commit `.cursor/mcp.json`.
